# Chrome Extension Conventions

## Manifest V3

- Use `"manifest_version": 3` — V2 is deprecated
- Service worker in `background.service_worker`, not `background.scripts`
- Use `chrome.storage.sync` for user settings (syncs across devices)
- Content scripts declared in manifest with appropriate `matches` patterns
- Request minimal permissions: `storage`, `activeTab`, `tabs`

## Content Scripts

- YouTube is an SPA — never assume a full page load. Always use `MutationObserver`
- Target `https://www.youtube.com/*` in manifest matches
- Use `document_idle` for `run_at` unless early injection is needed
- Clean up observers and listeners when the script is re-injected

## Message Passing

- Use `chrome.runtime.sendMessage` / `onMessage` for popup ↔ background
- Use `chrome.tabs.sendMessage` for background → content script
- Always type message payloads with discriminated unions:

```typescript
type Message =
  | { type: "TOGGLE_EXTENSION"; enabled: boolean }
  | { type: "UPDATE_FILTERS"; filters: FilterConfig }
  | { type: "GET_STATUS" };
```

## Storage

- Wrap `chrome.storage.sync` with typed async helpers
- Always provide defaults via `chrome.storage.sync.get({ key: defaultValue })`
- Listen to `chrome.storage.onChanged` to react to cross-tab changes

## Performance

- Minimize DOM queries — cache selectors where possible
- Debounce MutationObserver callbacks
- Avoid blocking the main thread — use `requestIdleCallback` for non-urgent work
- Never use `document.querySelectorAll("*")` — always scope queries tightly
